<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4535034>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 19. — A-F, Rhabdomeson progracile Wyse Jackson & Bancroft, 1995; A, longitudinal section showing axial cylinder, SMF 21.882; B, longitudinal section showing autozooecial chambers with hemisepta (arrow), SMF 21.882; C, tangential section showing autozooecial apertures, acanthostyles and paurostyles (arrow), SMF 21.872; D, tangential section showing acanthostyles and paurostyles (arrow), SMF 21.872; E, F, branch transverse section, SMF 21.875; G-I, Saffordotaxis incrassata (Ulrich, 1888), SMF 21.889; G, tangential section showing autozooecial apertures and aktinotostyles; H, I, branch longitudinal section. Scale bars: A, 2 mm; B, C, E, H, 1 mm; D, 0.2 mm; F, G, I, 0.5 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4535034/files/figure.png" .

